label.value: abnormal vacuole

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the number, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the vacuole(s) is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal cytoskeleton organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in a physically abnormal cytoskeleton.

label.value: large vacuoles present in decreased numbers during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains fewer, but larger, vacuoles than normal.

label.value: abnormal protein degradation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein degradation is abnormal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. Protein degradation, also known as protein catabolism, is any metabolic process that results in the destruction of the native, active configuration of a protein, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein degradation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of protein degradation is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein degradation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of protein degradation is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein degradation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein degradation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein degradation, also known as protein catabolism, is any metabolic process that results in the destruction of the native, active configuration of a protein, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein degradation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein degradation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein degradation, also known as protein catabolism, is any metabolic process that results in the destruction of the native, active configuration of a protein, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein degradation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein degradation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. Protein degradation, also known as protein catabolism, is any metabolic process that results in the destruction of the native, active configuration of a protein, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: nucleus mislocalized to cell cortex during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which a cell has a nucleus in an abnormal location at the cell cortex when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. The normal location is at the midpoint of the long axis of the cell.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: abnormal vacuole organization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which vacuole organization is abnormal. Vacuole organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a vacuole.

definition.value: Consider annotating to 'abnormal vacuolar morphology' (FYPO:0002257), but note that an abnormal vacuole organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal vacuolar morphology.

label.value: abnormal vacuole organization during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which vacuole organization is abnormal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. Vacuole organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a vacuole.

definition.value: Consider annotating to 'abnormal vacuolar morphology' (FYPO:0002257), but note that an abnormal vacuole organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal vacuolar morphology. This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: normal sodium import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which sodium ion import into the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: sensitive to arsenate

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to arsenate ions. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of arsenate that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal growth on arsenate

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing arsenate ions.

label.value: abnormal 6,7-dimethyl-8-ribityllumazine synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 6,7-dimethyl-8-ribityllumazine synthase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased 6,7-dimethyl-8-ribityllumazine synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 6,7-dimethyl-8-ribityllumazine synthase activity is decreased.

label.value: normal septation index in stationary phase

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the septation index is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a population in stationary phase. The septation index is the proportion of the population undergoing septation at any given time.

label.value: sensitive to non-ionic osmotic stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a non-ionic osmotic stress.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'sensitive to sorbitol' (FYPO:0000112) if sorbitol is used to cause osmotic stress.

label.value: decreased cellular glycerol level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of glycerol measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular glycerol level during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of glycerol measured in a cell during a cellular response to salt stress is lower than normal.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cell surface

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell surface is abnormal. The cell surface refers to the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell surface and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cell surface

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell surface is abolished. The cell surface refers to the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, multinucleate cell with elongated germ tube

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an elongated germ tube, and in which the nucleus divides at least once to produce a multinucleate cell. The cell does not divide, and eventually dies.

label.value: abnormally arrested meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the first meiotic nuclear division is arrested under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

label.value: microtubule bundles present in decreased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain fewer microtubule bundles than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 acetylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in telomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 methylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in telomeric regions does not occur.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased during interphase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body does not occur during interphase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal gamma-tubulin complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which gamma-tubulin complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at the silent mating-type cassettes is decreased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: constitutive protein kinase activity

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which the basal activity of a protein kinase is increased relative to normal. Basal protein kinase activity is the activity observed in the absence of a regulator. Abnormally elevated basal activity may or may not reach the levels observed in the normal activated state.

label.value: decreased cellular phytochelatin level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phytochelatin measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: delayed onset of protein phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of protein phosphorylation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, begins later than normal during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased polyuridylation-dependent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of polyuridylation-dependent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA is decreased. All RNA decapping may be decreased, or one or more specific RNA molecules may be selectively affected.

label.value: decreased chromatin silencing at centromere

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromeric regions is decreased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin or CENP-A-containing chromatin. See the GO cellular component terms 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin' (GO:0061638), and the biological process terms 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin organization' (GO:0061641).

label.value: centromeric outer repeat transcript-derived siRNA absent

value.value: An RNA metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which small interfering RNA transcripts derived from the centromere outer repeat region are absent.

definition.value: This term refers specifically to siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of RNA from the centromere outer repeat region. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences. For levels of RNA transcribed from an exogenous reporter gene placed in the outer repeat region, consider 'abnormal chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat region' (FYPO:0002346).

label.value: increased centromeric outer repeat transcript-derived siRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which small interfering RNA transcripts derived from the centromere outer repeat region are present at greater levels than normal.

definition.value: This term refers specifically to siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of RNA from the centromere outer repeat region. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences. For levels of RNA transcribed from an exogenous reporter gene placed in the outer repeat region, consider 'decreased chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat region' (FYPO:0003412).

label.value: normal centromeric outer repeat transcript-derived siRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of small interfering RNA transcripts derived from the centromere outer repeat region measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This term refers specifically to siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of RNA from the centromere outer repeat region. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to chromosome during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the centromere and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromosome during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromosome during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to chromosome during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromere outer repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere outer repeat regions of a chromosome is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: protein mislocalized to nucleoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is not normally found in the nucleoplasm is observed there.

definition.value: Note that this term can be used to annotate any case where a protein is found in the nucleoplasm in a mutant, but not in wild type. In some cases, there may be enough additional information to annotate to 'abnormal protein localization' (FYPO:0000443) or one of its descendants. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable swollen elongated septated vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is swollen, is elongated, and contains one or more septa. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

definition.value: The distinction between this phenotype and centrally constricted (dumbbell-shaped) cells (FYPO:0000779) is that swollen elongated cells do not have a constriction along the long axis. Swollen elongated cells may have a uniform diameter, or may be swollen only around the nucleus.
